message.text:
Green and Gold! Brave and Bold! Tamaraws, Never Fall! The UST Main Building will don the colors of our neighbor from Morayta, the Far Eastern University Tamaraws! 

The action starts here on September 19!

#UAAPSeason88 #LightOfHope #UST #FEU

message.text:
Green and Gold! Brave and Bold! Tamaraws, Never Fall! The UST Main Building will don the colors of our neighbor from Morayta, the Far Eastern University Tamaraws! 

The action starts here on September 19!

#UAAPSeason88 #LightOfHope #UST #FEU

message.text:
Dear FEU,

How is it that hybrid modality is implemented for us college students, yet shifting face-to-face classes to asynchronous or synchronous due to the strike seems impossible for you to do?

What’s more frustrating is that FEU High School, which is inside the main campus, and FEU Tech, which is just a crosswalk away, were able to shift to online modality. What makes us different from them? Yes, they may have different administrations, but everything is still under one name, right?

I hope the system can be more considerate about these issues. It’s not like we have our own terminal of jeepneys that we can easily ride, and we are not always capable of using Grab or motorcycle taxi apps. We’re just students. We’re already burdened by the high cost of tuition, and now we have to add this extra commuting expense to our budget.

PS: I dont usually post here, but this really annoys me. 🙂
